hop in here, Hal.

01:58.483 --> 02:00.484
Pour ourselves a drink.

02:00.486 --> 02:02.421
Could use one.

02:04.656 --> 02:05.955
Didn't make my quarter
this year.

02:05.957 --> 02:08.127
Probably not going
to make it.

02:09.594 --> 02:12.328
Oh, yeah.

02:12.330 --> 02:14.600
Not for lack of trying,
though.

02:15.633 --> 02:17.534
Bud stole my leads.

02:17.536 --> 02:19.235
- You're the boss.
- I'm the boss.

02:19.237 --> 02:21.370
Oh, you're the boss.

02:21.372 --> 02:22.972
He actually...
he gave them to me

02:22.974 --> 02:24.710
and then he took them
right back.

02:26.745 --> 02:28.448
Took them back.

02:28.813 --> 02:30.380
Yeah.

02:33.786 --> 02:35.788
God, I hate cold corn.

02:38.556 --> 02:40.389
Bud-oostie, huh?

02:40.391 --> 02:43.859
He's boffing his secretary while
he's got a wife at home.

02:43.861 --> 02:46.532
Oh, yeah, boss baby. Oh, yeah.

02:47.265 --> 02:48.600
I hate this job.

03:02.413 --> 03:03.682
Mrs. Elwood.

03:04.449 --> 03:05.817
Did you know?

03:07.686 --> 03:10.355
Look, I hate him just as much
as you do, trust me.

03:12.424 --> 03:14.558
Oh, I doubt it.

03:14.560 --> 03:16.329
Oh, no, no, please, please!

03:25.437 --> 03:27.436
- Oh, shit!
- Hey, Bud!

03:28.706 --> 03:30.776
Your wife's here.

03:34.712 --> 03:37.382
None of you can be trusted!

03:39.985 --> 03:41.885
None of you.

04:35.841 --> 04:37.276
Yeah...

04:46.084 --> 04:48.787
- I'm the boss, baby.
- Oh, you're the boss.

05:19.550 --> 05:21.788
Oh, I'm so fucking close.

05:32.831 --> 05:35.565
Oh, yeah, you're the boss!

05:35.567 --> 05:37.000
I'm the boss!

05:38.670 --> 05:40.372
Oh!

05:40.939 --> 05:42.805
Oh, jeez...

05:42.807 --> 05:44.444
You're not the man
I married.

05:50.649 --> 05:52.985
This place has changed you.

05:54.420 --> 05:56.519
Are you fucking nuts?

05:56.521 --> 05:58.457
Stay right where you are.

06:02.593 --> 06:04.594
Holly, honey,

06:04.596 --> 06:06.062
- I can explain...
- Shut up.

06:06.064 --> 06:09.565
You can't talk your way
out of this one.

06:09.567 --> 06:10.901
Please, I'm sorry!

06:10.903 --> 06:12.668
Apology accepted.

06:22.848 --> 06:24.650
I still love you.

06:35.593 --> 06:38.630
Every minute with you
has been a shrieking hell.

10:33.097 --> 10:35.864
When they said sisters,
I thought they meant

10:35.866 --> 10:37.767
a pair of nuns.

10:37.769 --> 10:39.435
No, sir, we're blood.

10:39.437 --> 10:42.008
I'm René,
this is Georgette.

10:43.475 --> 10:45.211
Can you help my daughter?

10:46.211 --> 10:48.180
We're the only ones
who can.

11:28.120 --> 11:30.056
It's best if
you wait outside.

11:38.230 --> 11:40.733
- Well, what can I do?
- Pray.

11:49.841 --> 11:51.310
She looks sick.

11:51.976 --> 11:54.143
She is sick.

11:54.145 --> 11:55.911
No, like she needs a doctor.

11:55.913 --> 11:58.350
You wanted to be a part
of the family business?

11:58.984 --> 12:00.382
Yeah.

12:00.384 --> 12:02.321
Then do like Grandma
taught us.

12:09.326 --> 12:10.962
Get her feet.

12:14.966 --> 12:16.331
Get her feet.

12:16.333 --> 12:17.967
Fine!

12:37.054 --> 12:38.588
Be ready.

12:38.590 --> 12:40.290
We'll trap it
with this.

12:40.292 --> 12:41.826
It's holy.

12:52.336 --> 12:56.040
I'm speaking to the entity
within this girl.

12:59.043 --> 13:01.980
This body is not yours.

13:06.183 --> 13:09.855
Leave now, or be trapped here
for all eternity.

13:12.591 --> 13:14.460
I will kill you.

13:17.095 --> 13:19.532
Please. I need a doctor.

13:21.600 --> 13:23.435
Please.

13:31.576 --> 13:34.109
Please. Help me.

13:34.111 --> 13:35.344
I need a doctor.

13:35.346 --> 13:37.247
Quick, the box.

13:37.249 --> 13:38.281
Give me the box.

13:38.283 --> 13:40.148
We should stop.

13:40.150 --> 13:42.020
It's too late.

13:43.053 --> 13:44.456
Please.

13:53.163 --> 13:54.998
Be gone!

13:55.000 --> 13:57.934
Be gone! Be gone!

13:59.203 --> 14:00.572
Don't break the circle.

14:02.474 --> 14:04.109
Don't break the circle.

14:05.110 --> 14:06.478
Georgette! Georgette!

14:24.528 --> 14:27.397
- So they're making this all up.
- I just want to finish.

14:27.399 --> 14:29.565
Are you calling
these people liars?

14:31.035 --> 14:32.535
I'm just saying they're
misinformed.

14:32.537 --> 14:34.938
Ah, misinformed.
If you're just joining us,

14:34.940 --> 14:37.105
welcome Georgette DuBois,

14:37.107 --> 14:38.473
professional skeptic.

14:38.475 --> 14:41.009
A new book,
<i>The Irrational God,</i>

14:41.011 --> 14:42.945
DuBois reveals a softer side.

14:42.947 --> 14:44.479
The book covers
her childhood,

14:44.481 --> 14:47.583
including her own
struggles with faith,

14:47.585 --> 14:50.085
and her discovery of science.

14:50.087 --> 14:53.690
She became famous for her
pioneering work in psychology.

14:53.692 --> 14:56.291
But these days,
her reputation stems mostly

14:56.293 --> 15:00.997
from her crusade against faith
healers and psychic mediums.

15:00.999 --> 15:03.498
What I do is a little bit
more complicated than that.

15:03.500 --> 15:06.169
You're on a mission
against the faithful.

15:06.171 --> 15:08.704
I'm referring to your run-in
with Father Heaven Lee,

15:08.706 --> 15:10.238
the exorcist.

15:10.240 --> 15:11.708
Oh, you mean
Harrison Miller Lee,

15:11.710 --> 15:13.475
the indicted criminal.

15:13.477 --> 15:16.212
There are those that say
he cured them.

15:16.214 --> 15:17.579
He's a parasite.

15:17.581 --> 15:20.382
Aren't some things
beyond explanation?

15:20.384 --> 15:22.986
Don't some things
require faith?

15:22.988 --> 15:24.520
It's one thing not to know,

15:24.522 --> 15:26.321
but we can't stop
looking for answers.

15:26.323 --> 15:28.992
You know, in the 19th century,
the work of serial killers

15:28.994 --> 15:32.027
was mistaken for evidence
of werewolves or vampires.

15:32.029 --> 15:34.129
We have to confront
the ugly truths.

15:34.131 --> 15:36.031
We can't keep hiding
from reality

15:36.033 --> 15:38.233
in some well-meaning
fairy tale.

15:38.235 --> 15:40.236
Well, you're not
buying it.

15:40.238 --> 15:42.738
I have 100 years
of medicine on my side.

15:42.740 --> 15:44.306
If your loved one
is speaking in tongues,

15:44.308 --> 15:46.108
then they're probably
having a seizure,

15:46.110 --> 15:47.642
not a message from God.

15:47.644 --> 15:50.512
You're building a career
by tearing down the institutions

15:50.514 --> 15:53.483
and beliefs that are
important to millions.

15:53.485 --> 15:57.589
Do you ever feel your skepticism
is alienating, Miss DuBois?

15:58.655 --> 16:00.455
I've always been
the odd man out.

16:00.457 --> 16:02.660
Maybe you fit in
by being the odd man.

16:03.293 --> 16:05.161
Maybe.

16:05.163 --> 16:08.097
You come from a long line
of fortune-tellers and mediums.

16:08.099 --> 16:09.598
Do you not?

16:09.600 --> 16:12.535
Is this crusade something
more personal, perhaps?

16:12.537 --> 16:15.238
<i>Is this just an act of defiance
against your family?</i>

16:15.240 --> 16:17.172
<i>No, it's quite the opposite,
actually.</i>

16:17.174 --> 16:19.108
<i>Nothing would make me happier
than finding evidence</i>

16:19.110 --> 16:20.443
<i>of the supernatural.</i>

16:20.445 --> 16:22.078
<i>Stay right there.</i>

16:22.080 --> 16:23.482
<i>When we return,
we'll hear from...</i>

16:47.739 --> 16:49.638
You look lost.

16:49.640 --> 16:51.239
Oh.

16:51.241 --> 16:53.478
I don't believe
I'm in the right place.

16:54.678 --> 16:56.512
Well, where are you
supposed to be?

16:56.514 --> 16:59.051
Is this the American Building?

17:01.251 --> 17:05.423
I'm here about the disturbances.
I believe we spoke on the phone.

17:06.257 --> 17:08.391
Oh, yeah.

17:08.393 --> 17:10.461
Yeah, I barely recognized
your voice.

17:12.363 --> 17:16.101
There was a doggy barking
pretty loudly in the background.

17:18.403 --> 17:20.268
Yes, I...

17:20.270 --> 17:22.371
I have quite a few,
actually.

17:22.373 --> 17:23.638
Yes, me too.

17:23.641 --> 17:25.407
Can't help collecting strays.

17:25.410 --> 17:27.311
Well, everybody
needs a good home.

17:28.779 --> 17:31.213
You know, I couldn't
have said that better myself.

17:31.215 --> 17:36.619
This place was originally
an apartment complex.

17:36.621 --> 17:40.222
And then a hotel
for about a minute.

17:40.224 --> 17:42.693
And offices ever since.

17:46.698 --> 17:48.898
There was a time when more than
a thousand people

17:48.900 --> 17:51.269
walked through this lobby
every morning.

17:52.202 --> 17:54.705
Yup, those were the days.

17:56.473 --> 17:58.841
This is actually
my first office job.

18:01.311 --> 18:02.745
Okey-dokey.

18:02.747 --> 18:04.682
Should we start
with the crime scene?

18:05.349 --> 18:06.717
Yes, please.

18:53.364 --> 18:56.431
Now, Mrs. Elwood
shot Mr. Elwood

18:56.433 --> 18:58.269
right next to where
you're standing.

19:01.372 --> 19:03.509
And then she turned
the gun on herself.

19:04.375 --> 19:06.411
A crime of passion.

19:07.979 --> 19:09.480
I guess so.

19:20.758 --> 19:23.162
Smaller than I imagined.

19:25.762 --> 19:31.299
What do coffins
and condoms have in common?

19:31.301 --> 19:33.736
Um... I don't know.
What?

19:33.738 --> 19:35.874
They're both for stiffs.

19:41.011 --> 19:43.347
So, what's the power
situation up here?

19:44.816 --> 19:47.318
Still purrs like a pussycat.

19:48.853 --> 19:51.319
Be a dear and go throw
the switch

19:51.321 --> 19:52.924
in that box by the elevator.

19:58.663 --> 20:00.496
So is the activity
always concentrated

20:00.498 --> 20:02.301
around the holidays?

20:03.433 --> 20:04.834
Yeah.

20:04.836 --> 20:07.239
Christmas always seems
to bring bad luck.

20:08.940 --> 20:10.741
Let's see.

20:12.509 --> 20:15.344
I mean, the architect died
the day the building opened,

20:15.346 --> 20:18.280
back in December 24th, 1919.

20:18.282 --> 20:20.284
Elevator crash.

20:21.986 --> 20:24.420
Jeez, talk about a bad sign.

20:24.422 --> 20:26.956
Yeah. It gets worse.

20:26.958 --> 20:31.661
Let's see, there was
the suicide in '38.

20:31.663 --> 20:34.799
Arson in '54.

20:35.566 --> 20:37.935
Outbreak in '76.

20:39.304 --> 20:41.903
There were rumors
of a curse.

20:41.905 --> 20:43.639
The girls in the typing pool

20:43.641 --> 20:45.940
claimed to have seen
weird things.

20:45.942 --> 20:50.645
But it wasn't until
the massacre of '84

20:50.647 --> 20:52.948
that business really
dried up.

20:52.950 --> 20:56.786
So management is hoping
that you will help

20:56.788 --> 20:58.757
to put an end
to the ghost stories.

21:00.325 --> 21:03.592
Well, there's an explanation
for everything.

21:03.594 --> 21:06.398
I'll leave it to
the professionals, then.

21:06.931 --> 21:08.463
If you need me,

21:08.465 --> 21:09.798
I'm going to be doing
my rounds.

21:09.800 --> 21:12.601
I left you a hard hat
and a walkie.

21:12.603 --> 21:15.103
Don't be afraid to use
either one.

21:15.105 --> 21:17.573
I like to be left alone
as much as possible.

21:17.575 --> 21:20.278
Less chance of contamination.

21:20.845 --> 21:22.713
Fine by me.

21:28.519 --> 21:29.951
Merry Christmas.

21:29.953 --> 21:32.423
No, I'm not a Christian.

21:34.625 --> 21:35.894
Oh, well.

21:39.529 --> 21:40.898
Happy Solstice.

